Simple Diffusion Model

A lightweight Diffusion Model for generating MNIST digit images using a U-Net architecture.

About The Project :

This project implements a minimal Diffusion Model capable of generating new handwritten digits (0–9).
The model is built using a U-Net backbone, sinusoidal time embeddings, and classifier-free guidance for better controlled generation.
You can also specify which digit the model should generate.

Note: MNIST is a simple dataset, so generated images are decent but not high-quality. Better datasets will produce stronger results.

Technologies Used :

Python
PyTorch
torchvision
tqdm

How to Run
1. Install dependencies
pip install torch torchvision tqdm

2. Run training
python train_diffusion.py

3. Outputs

Model checkpoints:
diffusion_model_epoch_X.pth

Generated samples per epoch:
generated_images_epoch_X.png

Features :

Simple and modular U-Net
Sinusoidal time embedding
Class-conditional generation (digits 0–9)
Classifier-Free Guidance
Cosine beta schedule
Clean and beginner-friendly code structure
Example: Generate a specific digit
(Example digit = 7)

images = diffusion.sample(
    n_samples=10,
    size=(1, 28, 28),
    device=device,
    guide_w=2.0
)

Dataset :

MNIST — 28×28 handwritten digit dataset

